d74c2492-a813-4231-b35b-cec3367f80c0.0bb220e6-484e-44e7-809f-cf67c7dda026.description=This workflow returns the artifact's properties and values using Artifact APIs. result\: propertyNameValuesList\: pipe separated list of property name and values ( where each property name and values would be ; seprated and multiple values would be , seprated) e.g. - property 1; value1,value2|property 2; value3|property 3; value3,value4|........ d74c2492-a813-4231-b35b-cec3367f80c0.361f5241-0b46-4dab-9248-4bbb1e9d53c8.description=This workflow adds/updates the component property using Artifact APIs. onlyUpdate\: yes/no yes - To update values of existing property (In this case input "valueType" is not required , This input will not be considered even if provided) no - To add/update property valueType - Value type of the property. It can have value from selection list "CSA-Property-ValueType". This Input is required only when Input "onlyUpdate" is selected as "no". values - One or more values dilimited by comma , (If user want to use some other separator for multiple values then needs to be pass as next input "separator") separator - A delimiter that separates elements in the values ( default dilimiter used is comma ,) d74c2492-a813-4231-b35b-cec3367f80c0.4ff6aad0-baeb-4aac-8b75-7f3492872272.prompt=Service Component Id d74c2492-a813-4231-b35b-cec3367f80c0.52381ac8-0eaf-4c17-b44f-571d54539c5b.description=
Subtracts two numbers

Inputs\:
value1 - The first value.
value2 - The second value.

Returns\:
The difference of the two numbers.

Responses\:
success - The operation completed successfully.
failure - Something went wrong.
d74c2492-a813-4231-b35b-cec3367f80c0.64d6c6d2-27c4-4efd-b55f-3df373cfeb26.prompt=User Identifier d74c2492-a813-4231-b35b-cec3367f80c0.6e05cc3f-54aa-4e6e-9dbf-1189d47fd3a2.prompt=Artifact ID d74c2492-a813-4231-b35b-cec3367f80c0.7ab18876-a61e-4669-9e8b-a61a5b93e39b.description=
Check to see if the value stored in a specified flow variable, denoted by key, is null.

Inputs\:
keyName - The key to check, i.e. the name of the flow variable.

Returns\: 
The value in the specified key, i.e. flow variable.

Responses\:
isNull - If the key is a null pointer, i.e. the flow variable doesn't have an assigned value.
notNull - If some value is stored in the key, i.e the flow variable has a value assigned.

Remove a Server from the Server Group

Input Parameters\:
serverGrpId - Server Group Component Id
serviceInstanceId - Service Instance Id of the Subscription
serverId - Server component Id 
reduceServers - Number of Servers to be removed - default to 1
userIdentifier - OO Application UUID to authorize a REST Call

Responses\:
   success -  if the command completes execution and its exit code is 0
   failure - otherwise

Result Fields\:
 NA
